Description: Native local file converter GUI
 T-Rex Converter is a native Debian GUI for local file conversion across
 images, video, audio, documents, PDFs, ebooks, SVG/vector, archives, OCR,
 subtitles, QR codes, and media metadata. It dispatches to system engines
 (FFmpeg, ImageMagick, LibreOffice, qpdf, Tesseract) and keeps everything
 on-device — no cloud upload.
 .
 The Recommends list pulls in optional engine binaries used by some pages:
 qrencode/zbar-tools (QR), inkscape + potrace + python3-tinycss2 (SVG /
 vector tools incl. pixmap → SVG trace), pandoc (Ebook module),
 libimage-exiftool-perl (Metadata cross-cut module).
 .
 Three Python dependencies are not packaged in Debian apt: PyMuPDF (fitz),
 qasync, and pdf2docx. After installing the .deb, install them in your
 user environment via pipx or a virtualenv (see README).
